WEBVTT

00:09.313 --> 00:11.533
[ Thelma Houston's
"Wake Up Everybody" playing ]

00:11.576 --> 00:14.057
Good morning, good morning,
good morning, Los Angeles!

00:14.101 --> 00:16.581
D.J. Tailwind Turner
with the burners,

00:16.625 --> 00:18.018
and it is a brand-new day,

00:18.061 --> 00:21.064
not like any of us know
what day it is anyway.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.979
To all the fine people
on the front lines,

00:23.023 --> 00:25.460
the hospital workers,
the first responders,

00:25.503 --> 00:27.375
to the couriers
and the truck drivers,

00:27.418 --> 00:30.160
the men and women
stocking food on our shelves,

00:30.204 --> 00:32.293
to the sick and the recovering,

00:32.336 --> 00:34.643
to our brothers and sisters
behind the prison walls,

00:34.686 --> 00:36.688
good morning, my friends!

00:36.732 --> 00:41.171
You are not forgotten.
You are not forgotten. Mm.

00:41.215 --> 00:43.130
Thelma Houston: ♪ This world
is in a whole lot of trouble ♪

00:43.173 --> 00:44.740
[ chime ]

00:44.783 --> 00:48.526
[ ringing ]

00:48.570 --> 00:51.007
♪ Because I believe that there's
a solution to all of this ♪

00:51.051 --> 00:52.574
[ chime ]Hey, oh.

00:52.617 --> 00:55.533
Finally.What took you so long?

00:55.577 --> 00:57.448
[ music stops ]What are you eating?

00:57.492 --> 00:58.580
Cap'n Crunch.I can't stop.

00:58.623 --> 01:01.365
It's a problem.Where are you?

01:01.409 --> 01:04.020
Back deck. Keep talking.
Gotta keep my heart rate up.

01:04.064 --> 01:05.500
[ mouth full ] Would youstop it? That's obnoxious.

01:05.543 --> 01:07.632
- Hey! You called me.
- You hear anything new?

01:07.676 --> 01:10.113
No, I got nothing.Trials cannot keepgetting pushed.

01:10.157 --> 01:12.333
I know. Choi's having
a heart attack.

01:12.376 --> 01:15.727
Multiple heart attacks.I don't care
about Choi's heart.

01:15.771 --> 01:17.077
I mean, obviously, yes,I care about Choi's heart,

01:17.120 --> 01:18.643
but I care more about--

01:18.687 --> 01:20.167
The American justice system
imploding

01:20.210 --> 01:22.778
and the end of the world
as we know it? Yeah, me, too.

01:22.821 --> 01:25.737
Would you seriouslystop it?

01:25.781 --> 01:27.957
Lola...

01:28.000 --> 01:32.179
I can't go to the gym,
and I'm going nutty here.

01:32.222 --> 01:35.182
I know. Me, too.I'm going stir crazy.

01:35.225 --> 01:38.402
- The backlog is...insane.
- It's insane.

01:38.446 --> 01:41.536
It was hard enough keeping upbefore this happened.

01:41.579 --> 01:44.974
If trials keep getting pushed,there is no way.

01:45.017 --> 01:48.108
I have another day of remote
fire sale plea bargains.

01:48.151 --> 01:50.501
It's a good time to be
a criminal.Don't start.

01:50.545 --> 01:53.330
But I want to.
Lola, I want to start.

01:53.374 --> 01:55.245
[ ring ]

01:55.289 --> 01:57.291
Yeah, hang on.That's Roxy.

01:57.334 --> 01:59.206
[ chime ]Hi, Mama.

01:59.249 --> 02:00.772
Hello, daughter!

02:00.816 --> 02:03.732
Lo...go good.

02:03.775 --> 02:05.690
- You, too.
- Me, too, what?

02:05.734 --> 02:08.911
No, Mama, that was Mark.

02:08.954 --> 02:11.957
I can't see him. Am I supposed
to be able to see him?

02:12.001 --> 02:14.264
And, Lo, go easy
on the Cap'n Crunch.

02:14.308 --> 02:16.179
Shut up.

02:16.223 --> 02:18.181
Mama, how's Daddy doing?

02:18.225 --> 02:21.315
Oh, he's fine. He's cleaning outthe crawl space

02:21.358 --> 02:24.013
and listening
to Bill Withers records.

02:24.056 --> 02:27.756
And if you wanna convince me
to stay inside...

02:27.799 --> 02:29.410
[ singsongy ]
you're wasting your breath!

02:29.453 --> 02:31.977
Mama, you can't be
going out all day

02:32.021 --> 02:33.283
delivering care packages.

02:33.327 --> 02:35.590
They need my help!

02:35.633 --> 02:38.593
Mom, youshould be having things
brought to you,

02:38.636 --> 02:40.464
not the other way around.

02:40.508 --> 02:42.162
You have
an underlying condition.

02:42.205 --> 02:44.120
It's dangerous.

02:44.164 --> 02:46.166
[ ring ]Oh. One second.

02:46.209 --> 02:48.255
I'm sorry.[ chime ]

02:48.298 --> 02:51.432
Carmichael, you're late.

02:51.475 --> 02:53.477
Mom, I have to--
I have a meeting.

02:53.521 --> 02:54.957
[ loudly ]
Wait. How--How's Robin?

02:55.000 --> 02:58.265
You don't have to keep yelling.He is fine.

02:58.308 --> 03:00.789
The Bureau doesn't want himleaving D.C.

03:00.832 --> 03:04.184
He sends his love, okay?
I gotta go.

03:04.227 --> 03:07.404
Mama, stay inside.

03:07.448 --> 03:10.625
WOMAN:Don't forget to breathe, people.

03:10.668 --> 03:12.453
[ exhales deeply ]
I'm doing yoga literally

03:12.496 --> 03:14.542
three times a day.
I'm addicted.

03:14.585 --> 03:16.196
I am not mad at it.

03:16.239 --> 03:17.762
[ chuckles ]

03:17.806 --> 03:20.330
That's it. Flower your buttocks.

03:20.374 --> 03:22.898
I need to flower my buttocks.
Can I call you later?

03:22.941 --> 03:25.248
Wait, wait.Did you get my package?

03:25.292 --> 03:27.207
- Mm-hmm.
- So what'd you think?

03:27.250 --> 03:29.992
I think it's intriguing,

03:30.035 --> 03:31.602
and I think we'll be
testing it later.

03:31.646 --> 03:34.518
Mm.Okay, Cat Cow.
Everyone inhale.

03:34.562 --> 03:37.434
- Okay, gotta go.
- Wait. I'm--I'm watching.

03:37.478 --> 03:41.308
[ chime ]Now press your chest forward
like this and inhale.

03:41.351 --> 03:44.920
Think like a cat who needs
a really good stretch.[ ring ]

03:44.963 --> 03:47.052
Tilt the tailbone up...

03:47.096 --> 03:48.228
[ electronic whoosh ]

03:49.881 --> 03:51.405
What partof "shelter-in-place"

03:51.448 --> 03:53.798
do you not understand?

03:53.842 --> 03:56.323
Hey, outside exercise
is a specific exemption.

03:56.366 --> 03:59.848
- Thank you very much.
- I know. I just--Be careful.

03:59.891 --> 04:01.893
Em, people see a black man
running down the street

04:01.937 --> 04:03.852
with a mask on, they tend
to cross to the other side.

04:03.895 --> 04:06.855
- [ chuckles ]
- I miss you.

04:06.898 --> 04:10.032
I miss you, too,but I have to--Ugh.

04:10.075 --> 04:11.294
Hey, listen, have you been
reading the latest?

04:11.338 --> 04:13.905
Jails and prisons,
it's just like...

04:13.949 --> 04:15.037
- They're trying.
- ...it's not good.

04:15.080 --> 04:17.126
- We're trying, Luke.
- You look good.

04:17.169 --> 04:19.998
- Ugh.
- Let's have a date.

04:20.042 --> 04:23.001
Luke, I am buried. Buried!

04:23.045 --> 04:24.655
My calendar changesevery time I log in,

04:24.699 --> 04:27.528
and Carol just keepsjust throwing files at me.

04:27.571 --> 04:29.225
No, come on.
We'll make the same thing.

04:29.269 --> 04:31.053
We'll eat together.
Who knows where it'll lead?

04:31.096 --> 04:35.057
Oh, I am at my brother's house,helping him and his wife

04:35.100 --> 04:36.798
with the kids.
- The little terrors.

04:36.841 --> 04:39.801
Who come into my room at anymoment without notice. Just--

04:39.844 --> 04:42.412
Okay, then we'll have
a late, late dinner.

04:42.456 --> 04:45.067
Just finish your run.Just run it off.

04:45.110 --> 04:47.374
- Just...run it off.
- Okay.

04:47.417 --> 04:49.289
[ both laugh ]

04:49.332 --> 04:51.073
- Mwah.
- Bye.

04:51.116 --> 04:52.770
Bye.

04:52.814 --> 04:55.120
Hanni El Khatib:
♪ I can't believe I survived

04:55.164 --> 04:57.297
[ chime ]You need to give yoga
another chance.

04:57.340 --> 04:58.863
It helps with the anxiety.

04:58.907 --> 05:01.518
Sara, I do not experienceanxiety. Please fix yourself.

05:01.562 --> 05:03.738
Just because you don't
call it anxiety...

05:03.781 --> 05:05.609
I am labeling spices,

05:05.653 --> 05:10.005
and I am experimenting witha new way to fold my towels.

05:10.048 --> 05:11.528
It's very relaxing.

05:11.572 --> 05:14.923
I only have three
Instacart deliveries today.

05:14.966 --> 05:19.319
So let's do corona cocktails
after to unwind.

05:19.362 --> 05:20.842
It makes me nervousyou doing that.

05:20.885 --> 05:24.411
What? I've got my gloves,
my mask,

05:24.454 --> 05:26.891
and I have a car payment,
Sherri.

05:26.935 --> 05:28.937
Transcript work has
totally dried up.

05:28.980 --> 05:31.896
[ muffled ]
I will call you at 7.[ chime ]

05:31.940 --> 05:33.768
BENNER: Police are still
making arrests.

05:33.811 --> 05:35.552
We could do
all the arraignments

05:35.596 --> 05:37.249
and prelims we want
on video.

05:37.293 --> 05:39.034
We're just delaying
the deluge.

05:39.077 --> 05:40.775
Once the emergency order
is lifted...[ chime ]

05:40.818 --> 05:43.343
Carmichael. Good.
That's a quorum.

05:43.386 --> 05:46.171
Jonas, have you been
motorcycling?

05:46.215 --> 05:48.391
The freeways are glorious!

05:48.435 --> 05:51.873
Albert has an invasionof gall mites.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.048
- Gall what?
- Yeah!

05:53.091 --> 05:55.137
The leaves of my fuchsia
are pimpling.

05:55.180 --> 05:58.358
We're talking
about the backlog.Good. We need to do something.

05:58.401 --> 05:59.924
We are doing something.Bail at zero,

05:59.968 --> 06:01.317
O.R. releasefor low-level offenders.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.580
All due respect, Jonas,
it's not enough.

06:03.624 --> 06:05.930
The conditions inside
of the jails are appalling.

06:05.974 --> 06:08.933
21 more inmates tested positive
in the last day,

06:08.977 --> 06:11.066
four more guards.
We have to do something.

06:11.109 --> 06:13.460
- I have a thought.
- Hmm.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.679
- What a surprise.
- Oh, go mute yourself, Jonas.

06:15.723 --> 06:20.641
- Out with it, Carmichael.
- Okay.

06:20.684 --> 06:21.903
[ siren wailing,
horn honks in distance ]

06:21.946 --> 06:23.948
How is it in there?Things getting any better?

06:23.992 --> 06:26.211
Oh, yeah, things are great,
Ms. Lopez.

06:26.255 --> 06:29.432
I'm taking Japanese lessons,
practicing calligraphy.

06:29.476 --> 06:31.608
Kurt, seriously.

06:31.652 --> 06:33.349
Seriously?

06:33.393 --> 06:36.831
I need you to get me the hell
out of here, Ms. Lopez.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.747
I can't get a bar of soap.
Toilet paper is a myth.

06:39.790 --> 06:41.836
Courts arestill very chaotic.

06:41.879 --> 06:43.446
They--They keep pushing
trial dates back.

06:43.490 --> 06:45.405
How long?

06:45.448 --> 06:47.189
Right now, 60 days.

06:47.232 --> 06:49.800
60 days?! No, they can't
do that, right?

06:49.844 --> 06:53.195
They are doing it.I'm gonna talk to the DDA

06:53.238 --> 06:55.502
and see if I can...
shake this loose.

06:55.545 --> 06:57.678
Look, Kurt, I know that youdon't have money for bail--

06:57.721 --> 07:01.986
I didn't do this thing.
He put his hands on me.

07:02.030 --> 07:03.814
I mean, we're brothers.
We argue.

07:03.858 --> 07:04.989
We've been
our entire lives,

07:05.033 --> 07:07.339
and now he calls
the police on me?

07:07.383 --> 07:10.430
The car's mine, too. Both of
our names are on the title.

07:10.473 --> 07:13.433
And I am gonna argue that point.We have a good case here.

07:13.476 --> 07:16.827
My girlfriend Rosa--she's due
in, like, five weeks.

07:16.871 --> 07:19.482
You didn't say anythingabout y-your g--

07:19.526 --> 07:22.050
Yeah, I didn't think
I'd still be in here.

07:22.093 --> 07:24.226
She is all alone,
Ms. Lopez.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.402
This is...

07:26.446 --> 07:28.273
This is killing me.

07:28.317 --> 07:29.666
I need to see her,

07:29.710 --> 07:32.364
and there are
no visits anymore.

07:32.408 --> 07:35.063
Can we maybe do this
with her?

07:35.106 --> 07:37.500
This video thing--
could you make that happen?

07:37.544 --> 07:39.676
[ Phosphorescent's "This Land
Is Your Land" playing ]

07:39.720 --> 07:41.417
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

07:41.461 --> 07:44.202
♪This land is your land

07:44.246 --> 07:47.641
♪ This land is my land

07:47.684 --> 07:49.381
♪ California

07:49.425 --> 07:52.776
CAMPBELL: Look, online trials
are simply not practical.

07:52.820 --> 07:55.475
Why not? We are already
doing arraignment.

07:55.518 --> 07:57.477
- The Constitution, is why not.
- Because of the Constitution.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.522
The right to face
your accuser.The right to a jury.

07:59.566 --> 08:01.437
Both of you settle down.

08:01.481 --> 08:02.873
What if the defendant'snetwork dies?

08:02.917 --> 08:04.919
What if he can't talkto counsel?Then we'll wait.

08:04.962 --> 08:07.182
The technology
isn't the point, Jonas.

08:07.225 --> 08:09.532
It's the entire point.The spirit of what
the founders intended

08:09.576 --> 08:11.534
is still maintained.
- Says you.

08:11.578 --> 08:13.580
I like it. Clients can waive
certain guarantees,

08:13.623 --> 08:16.844
or they can sit in jail
for God knows how long.

08:16.887 --> 08:19.542
They're ganging up on us.It's possible
they're right, Jonas.

08:19.586 --> 08:20.717
It's not much point
in trying the accused

08:20.761 --> 08:22.502
if they're no longer
alive.

08:22.545 --> 08:25.069
Little dark there, Albert.

08:25.113 --> 08:27.463
Mm-hmm. These are
dark times, Abigail.

08:27.507 --> 08:30.988
- Yeah.
- So...we agree.

08:31.032 --> 08:34.426
Carmichael, since you're
so keen, you'll be up first.

08:34.470 --> 08:36.385
- Find me a test case.
- I already have one in mind.

08:36.428 --> 08:38.256
Good, because you're going to
need to figure out

08:38.300 --> 08:40.302
how the hell this is gonna work.

08:40.345 --> 08:45.829
♪♪♪

08:45.873 --> 08:49.137
Captioned by
Los Angeles Distribution
and Broadcasting, Inc.

08:53.141 --> 08:54.534
[ Carmen Rodgers' "Just Believe"playing ]

08:54.577 --> 08:58.755
D.J. TAILWIND: Yeah.Don't get up. Don't get dressed.

08:58.799 --> 09:00.844
Give yourself a break.
Five more minutes.

09:00.888 --> 09:03.368
Ain't nobody outside
to play with anyway.

09:03.412 --> 09:05.414
So stay warm
with the one you love

09:05.457 --> 09:07.416
or the one you're with,

09:07.459 --> 09:08.722
or the one
you're dreaming about.

09:08.765 --> 09:10.811
Stay right where you are.

09:10.854 --> 09:14.031
Stay...right where...you...are.

09:14.075 --> 09:17.208
♪ You say that
life's got you feeling down ♪

09:17.252 --> 09:20.211
Whoo! [ laughs ]
Well, that was a first.

09:20.255 --> 09:22.083
I think it works.

09:22.126 --> 09:25.608
Oh. It works. It works.

09:25.652 --> 09:28.524
[ sighs ] I have to say,
all this yoga,

09:28.568 --> 09:32.746
my body is doing thingsit has never done before.

09:32.789 --> 09:35.139
Oh, really? Like what?

09:35.183 --> 09:37.620
No, seriously.
Give me every detail.

09:37.664 --> 09:39.274
[ giggles ]

09:39.317 --> 09:42.756
I think I need a few minutes
to, you know, regroup.

09:42.799 --> 09:44.627
Aw.[ chime ]

09:44.671 --> 09:47.021
Oh, damn.
I've got a meeting.

09:47.064 --> 09:50.546
- Well, put a shirt on.
- I'm working on it.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.853
All right.
How do I look?

09:52.896 --> 09:54.637
Little flushed, maybe.

09:54.681 --> 09:56.204
I'll see ya.

09:56.247 --> 09:59.337
♪ Believe [ electronic whoosh ]

09:59.381 --> 10:00.600
[ chimes ]Lopez, hey.

10:00.643 --> 10:02.427
- Hey.
- Nice home office.

10:02.471 --> 10:05.692
I am in a closet hidingfrom a nephew invasion.

10:05.735 --> 10:08.869
Where are you? Are you--Are you in your bedroom?

10:08.912 --> 10:09.870
Yeah, sorry.
I was just, um...

10:09.913 --> 10:12.437
Oh, no, don't...tell me.

10:12.481 --> 10:16.093
- Do you need a minute?
- Amy Quinn says hi.

10:16.137 --> 10:17.660
[ chuckles ]No, she doesn't.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.183
- [ scoffs ]
- Hi, back.

10:19.227 --> 10:21.272
Okay. So my client,Kurt Beto--

10:21.316 --> 10:23.927
Hang on. Choi just sent
the file over, and it's...

10:23.971 --> 10:25.929
- There's no case here, Mark.
- Carjacking.

10:25.973 --> 10:28.105
- Nope. Family feud.
- Not according to the prelim.

10:28.149 --> 10:30.542
Uh, the prelim wasthe arresting officer

10:30.586 --> 10:32.457
spouting backwhat the victim told him--

10:32.501 --> 10:34.459
Victim is Joey Beto,
your client's brother.

10:34.503 --> 10:36.070
It was a sibling squabble,not a carjacking.

10:36.113 --> 10:37.637
Totally overcharged.

10:37.680 --> 10:39.769
So...let's talk aboutan O.R. release.

10:39.813 --> 10:41.510
Lopez, your guy
has a violent past.

10:41.553 --> 10:43.817
Orwe can wrap it upat misdemeanor joyriding,

10:43.860 --> 10:45.732
10851. No further custody.

10:45.775 --> 10:48.299
- Time served.
- It's not gonna happen, Lopez.

10:48.343 --> 10:49.561
[ scoffs ]

10:49.605 --> 10:52.216
[ ringing ]

10:52.260 --> 10:53.957
- I have another call.
- Yep.

10:54.001 --> 10:55.655
So...cool.[ chime ]

10:55.698 --> 10:59.180
Hey.Everyone wants
more toilet paper.

10:59.223 --> 11:00.616
Why aren't you dressed?

11:00.660 --> 11:02.009
This woman texted
that she was pregnant,

11:02.052 --> 11:04.054
and she had to have
baby dills,

11:04.098 --> 11:06.230
so I went to, like,
six different stores

11:06.274 --> 11:09.059
to find her baby dills.
She hasn't even said thank you.

11:09.103 --> 11:12.454
- Oh, my God.
- I need to get dressed.

11:12.497 --> 11:14.456
- Do you know what I miss?
- [ boy giggles ]

11:14.499 --> 11:16.980
Stop it! Sorry.The little terrors found me.

11:17.024 --> 11:20.462
Fun! I miss fun.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.594
- Stop it! Sara--
- [ boy shouting indistinctly ]

11:22.638 --> 11:25.162
Sara, I'll call you.I'll see you in a few minutes.[ boys yelling indistinctly ]

11:25.206 --> 11:27.338
What did I say?! Guys!

11:27.382 --> 11:28.513
[ electronic whoosh ]

11:28.557 --> 11:30.341
[ taps keyboard ]

11:30.385 --> 11:31.734
[ click, chime ]

11:31.778 --> 11:33.431
In the matter of
the People vs. Kurt Beto,

11:33.475 --> 11:35.999
I would have preferred you wouldcome to me with a plea deal.

11:36.043 --> 11:37.958
- Couldn't reach a resolution.
- We tried, Your Honor.

11:38.001 --> 11:40.177
- Sara, are we on the record?
- Yes, I'm typing.

11:40.221 --> 11:42.092
Yes, you are inJudge Carmichael's chambers,

11:42.136 --> 11:44.094
standing right in front
of her desk, in fact.

11:44.138 --> 11:45.705
Okay, good to know.

11:45.748 --> 11:49.143
And Judge Carmichael is
very displeased with you two.

11:49.186 --> 11:51.623
- I would have expected--
- "Displeased"? Really?

11:51.667 --> 11:53.495
Is that how you're
gonna talk to counsel?

11:53.538 --> 11:55.497
- Come on.
- Excuse me?

11:55.540 --> 11:57.499
Wait. Callan, is thisyour first time appearing

11:57.542 --> 11:58.761
in frontof Judge Carmichael?

11:58.805 --> 11:59.980
- First time.
- It doesn't matter.

12:00.023 --> 12:00.981
- [ gasps ] Oh! Besties!
- Wow.

12:01.024 --> 12:03.940
Ah. Mnh-mnh.Everyone, be quiet!

12:03.984 --> 12:05.289
Your Honor.

12:05.333 --> 12:08.031
Thank you, Sherri. Ms. Lopez?

12:08.075 --> 12:09.903
I'd like to ask, Your Honor,
to consider a motion

12:09.946 --> 12:11.774
to release my client O.R.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.776
All right.
People, what's your position?

12:13.820 --> 12:16.736
Kurt Beto viciously attacked
his brother, Joey Beto,

12:16.779 --> 12:19.086
who is an upstanding businessmanwith no prior criminal record.

12:19.129 --> 12:21.175
He also jacked
his vehicle.

12:21.218 --> 12:24.134
My client is not violent.He is a street artist--

12:24.178 --> 12:25.962
He has a record
for assault, Lopez.

12:26.006 --> 12:28.095
Two years ago, he threw a punchwhen he was high.

12:28.138 --> 12:29.400
He has been cleanever since.

12:29.444 --> 12:31.359
He was clean whenthis incident happened.

12:31.402 --> 12:32.752
They're brothers.
They argue.

12:32.795 --> 12:36.059
Your Honor, my clienthas a pregnant girlfriend.

12:36.103 --> 12:39.454
Given the catastrophic
health conditions

12:39.497 --> 12:41.717
where he is being detained--
- How far along is she?

12:41.761 --> 12:43.240
Due in five weeks,currently self-quarantined

12:43.284 --> 12:44.459
and alone, Your Honor.

12:44.502 --> 12:46.330
The public's safety
should be

12:46.374 --> 12:48.506
the court's
primary concern here.

12:48.550 --> 12:50.770
The accused is under 50.
He has no underlying condition,

12:50.813 --> 12:53.076
and he has a felony assault
on his record, period.

12:53.120 --> 12:55.426
Thank you. I have heard enough.

12:55.470 --> 13:00.518
Perhaps we should go to trial
right away.

13:00.562 --> 13:02.694
I have been given the latitude

13:02.738 --> 13:03.870
to explore conducting trials
remotely.

13:03.913 --> 13:06.263
I think this would be
a great test case.

13:06.307 --> 13:07.787
- What?
- Really?

13:07.830 --> 13:11.268
A bench trial. We will
live-stream the whole thing

13:11.312 --> 13:12.966
so the proceedings
will remain public.

13:13.009 --> 13:15.403
Obviously,
it would involve waiving

13:15.446 --> 13:17.231
certain constitutional rights?

13:17.274 --> 13:18.798
- Uh, yeah.
- The right to trial by jury,

13:18.841 --> 13:20.974
the right to face your accuser
in person,

13:21.017 --> 13:23.498
the right to have your attorney
in the same room for a start,

13:23.541 --> 13:27.415
butflip side, it would also
guarantee a speedy trial,

13:27.458 --> 13:30.810
which it is clear
Mr. Beto needs in this case.

13:30.853 --> 13:32.724
- Your Honor, this is not--
- Talk to your bosses.

13:32.768 --> 13:35.031
Talk to your client,
and get back to me.

13:35.075 --> 13:36.598
But-- Nicole Willis:
♪ Ready for the call

13:36.641 --> 13:38.295
♪ Whenever you're ready

13:38.339 --> 13:39.819
Go.[ chime ]

13:39.862 --> 13:43.257
Go, go, go. Now.

13:43.300 --> 13:45.520
[ chime ]Am I muted? Go!

13:45.563 --> 13:47.739
[ chime ]

13:47.783 --> 13:49.872
If this
virtual trial thing works,

13:49.916 --> 13:51.439
it'll go a long way
to solving the problem.

13:51.482 --> 13:52.744
Agreed.

13:52.788 --> 13:53.963
Having nightmares
about the backlog.

13:54.007 --> 13:55.835
Seriously, 2 a.m.,

13:55.878 --> 13:57.358
I'm lying awake.
I'm a mess.

13:57.401 --> 13:59.577
So you're on board?

13:59.621 --> 14:01.797
They will need to waive
the right to appeal,

14:01.841 --> 14:05.540
not on the legal merits,
on the procedure.On the procedure. Agreed.

14:05.583 --> 14:07.977
[ ring ]There's Watkins. Great.
I told him to call.

14:08.021 --> 14:09.892
Stay on for this. Hang on.[ chime ]

14:09.936 --> 14:12.895
Luke, you got Callan too.

14:12.939 --> 14:15.898
- Hey, bud.
- Hey.

14:15.942 --> 14:17.813
Tell him what you pitched me
in your email.

14:17.857 --> 14:20.163
I wanna go down to
county jail, Men's Central.

14:20.207 --> 14:22.862
Now?I spoke to a buddy--
a sheriff who works there.

14:22.905 --> 14:25.603
He says
it's utter chaos.

14:25.647 --> 14:27.083
They're struggling with
the sheer volume of releases.

14:27.127 --> 14:28.476
I wanna go down
and make sure

14:28.519 --> 14:29.607
that no one falls
through the cracks.

14:29.651 --> 14:31.522
- Are you insane?
- No way.

14:31.566 --> 14:34.874
I need to do something.I just can't sit here.

14:34.917 --> 14:37.050
- Uh, yeah, you can.
- The answer is no.

14:37.093 --> 14:39.530
Goodbye.[ chime ]

14:41.271 --> 14:44.666
The linen closet?!
Kids are hiding my papers.

14:44.709 --> 14:46.233
I really hope you didn'tread this!

14:46.276 --> 14:49.279
It's a double homicide!

14:49.323 --> 14:51.629
How you holding up,
Rosa?

14:51.673 --> 14:53.501
I pee all the time.My back is killing me.

14:53.544 --> 14:55.851
The father of my babyis in jail during a pandemic,

14:55.895 --> 14:58.723
and I can't even
drink wine.

14:58.767 --> 15:00.987
So good.

15:01.030 --> 15:03.163
[ chime ]MAN:
Okay, you've got five minutes.

15:03.206 --> 15:04.904
[ clears throat ]

15:04.947 --> 15:07.471
There's Kurt.
Can you see him?

15:07.515 --> 15:10.822
Oh, I promised the babyI wasn't gonna cry.

15:10.866 --> 15:15.131
Hey, I'm gonna mute myself
and just step off

15:15.175 --> 15:17.960
so you--so you two
can talk, okay?

15:20.267 --> 15:21.703
Hey, beautiful.

15:21.746 --> 15:23.400
- [ sniffles ]
- Okay?

15:23.444 --> 15:26.447
- Let me see the belly.
- [ cries ]

15:28.275 --> 15:31.582
- Oh, my God.
- [ laughs ] Can you see it?

15:31.626 --> 15:32.801
It's beautiful.

15:32.844 --> 15:35.195
[ laughs ]

15:35.238 --> 15:37.545
- [ exhales deeply ]
- It's okay.

15:37.588 --> 15:39.503
I'm all right. [ sniffles ]
It's okay.

15:39.547 --> 15:41.027
Do you have a feveror anything like that?

15:41.070 --> 15:43.638
Nothing. Nothing yet.

15:43.681 --> 15:45.727
And you're gonna dothe trial?

15:45.770 --> 15:47.511
- It looks like it.
- I can watch, right?

15:47.555 --> 15:50.993
- I can log in?
- Uh, Ms. Lopez. Ms. Lopez?

15:51.037 --> 15:53.039
Could she...

15:53.082 --> 15:54.997
[ chime ]Yep, I can send you
a link, Rosa.

15:55.041 --> 15:57.304
Okay. Thank you.

15:59.001 --> 16:00.263
Ms. Lopez?

16:00.307 --> 16:03.571
Kurt's gonna bea great dad.

16:03.614 --> 16:04.833
I know.

16:04.876 --> 16:07.401
An incredible dad.

16:07.444 --> 16:10.534
But he needs to be backfor when his son gets here.

16:10.578 --> 16:12.797
He needs to raise his son,
okay?

16:12.841 --> 16:14.799
We need him. Okay?

16:14.843 --> 16:17.019
- I know.
- Do you?

16:17.063 --> 16:19.804
I do. I know, Rosa. I know.

16:19.848 --> 16:20.980
[ Katie Pruitt's"Change Is Gonna Come" playing ]

16:21.023 --> 16:22.677
I know.

16:22.720 --> 16:23.939
♪ Dark is coming, and the daylight's almost gone ♪

16:23.983 --> 16:25.027
[ gate buzzes, door opens ]

16:25.071 --> 16:27.377
- I love you.
- I love you.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.597
MAN: Kurt, time's up. Let's go.

16:29.640 --> 16:30.990
- Thank you, Ms. Lopez.
- You're welcome!

16:31.033 --> 16:32.687
[ whispers ] Bye.

16:32.730 --> 16:34.297
[ sobs ]

16:34.341 --> 16:35.255
[ gate buzzes, door opens ]

16:35.298 --> 16:37.387
[ chimes ]It's all right.

16:37.431 --> 16:39.433
Gonna figure this out.

16:39.476 --> 16:43.654
♪ But a change is gonna come

16:47.180 --> 16:49.008
I want my restaurants back--
all of them.

16:49.051 --> 16:50.574
You are doing great.

16:50.618 --> 16:51.575
My mother wouldn't
let me in the kitchen.

16:51.619 --> 16:53.099
I never learned
how to cook.

16:53.142 --> 16:55.362
Well, maybe that's one goodthing to come out of all this.

16:55.405 --> 16:57.320
You wouldn't say that if you had
to eat yesterday's risotto.

16:57.364 --> 17:00.497
- So you heard from Choi?
- He's on board.

17:00.541 --> 17:02.325
And it's Mark Callan
for the People?

17:02.369 --> 17:05.589
Yep.If we weren't running short
on lawyers and judges,

17:05.633 --> 17:08.288
I wouldn't approve it.
- Lisa, we'll be fine.

17:08.331 --> 17:10.507
Better be. What are you
wearing for robes?

17:10.551 --> 17:13.554
- I hadn't thought about it.
- Oh, fudge!

17:13.597 --> 17:16.122
I forgot to take the phyllo
out of the freezer.

17:16.165 --> 17:18.646
[ snickers ]

17:18.689 --> 17:21.257
Ohh! Carmichael.
This is the internet.

17:21.301 --> 17:24.304
Anything you wear or say
or do is going to be seen

17:24.347 --> 17:26.480
and captured by a Russian
troll farm and posted,

17:26.523 --> 17:29.048
so don't screw it up.

17:29.091 --> 17:32.529
[ ringing ]Lisa, can I call youright back?

17:32.573 --> 17:35.097
Sure. But be warned.

17:35.141 --> 17:37.230
[ ring ]Pastry makes me
swear like a sailor.

17:37.273 --> 17:38.753
- Okay.
- Ugh!

17:38.796 --> 17:40.407
[ chime ]

17:40.450 --> 17:41.364
Marky Mark!

17:41.408 --> 17:43.497
Your Honor.

17:43.540 --> 17:46.239
See? That's why
we need to talk. Let's go.

17:46.282 --> 17:48.067
Why are we doing this?

17:48.110 --> 17:51.461
Because it's our thing, and I
need for this to feel real,

17:51.505 --> 17:53.768
feel normal
now more than ever.

17:53.811 --> 17:55.291
How's your dad?How's Roxy?

17:55.335 --> 17:58.773
[ sighs ] He's good.
The other one scares me.

17:58.816 --> 18:01.167
She keeps trying
to deliver supplies to people

18:01.210 --> 18:02.211
when she needs to be
staying at home.

18:02.255 --> 18:04.735
Roxy will be Roxy.

18:04.779 --> 18:06.346
See? Isn't this nice?

18:06.389 --> 18:09.000
If you like stairs.

18:09.044 --> 18:12.047
Okay. So, this trial,
our first,

18:12.091 --> 18:13.614
we need to set
some ground rules.

18:13.657 --> 18:15.703
Lola, I'm not gonna riskany ex-parte.

18:15.746 --> 18:18.140
Rule number one--do not
try to make me laugh.

18:18.184 --> 18:20.099
Lola.And do not expect
any special favors.

18:20.142 --> 18:22.536
As a matter of fact,
you better bring your "A" game,

18:22.579 --> 18:23.798
because I plan on being
really hard on you.

18:23.841 --> 18:25.539
Oh, okay. All right.

18:25.582 --> 18:27.193
Well, then no eye rollingin my direction

18:27.236 --> 18:29.456
or that look that says,"I know better than you"

18:29.499 --> 18:31.501
that you seem to reserve
just for me.

18:31.545 --> 18:33.373
I do not give you
that look,

18:33.416 --> 18:36.985
and I am serious, Mark.
Don't try to make me laugh.

18:41.424 --> 18:43.122
BOTH: Deal.

18:45.646 --> 18:47.822
[ ring ]

18:47.865 --> 18:49.171
[ ring ]

18:49.215 --> 18:50.216
[ electronic whoosh ]

18:50.259 --> 18:53.132
Ooh. Look at you.What's going on?

18:53.175 --> 18:54.829
Laundry day?

18:54.872 --> 18:57.484
[ chuckles ] I'm going downtown.I wanna look presentable.

18:57.527 --> 19:00.139
Oh. Okay. But...

19:00.182 --> 19:02.141
I thought the D.A.furloughed all the law clerks.

19:02.184 --> 19:04.012
They did. I'm going
to Men's Central.

19:04.055 --> 19:06.057
Is Choi sending you?

19:06.101 --> 19:08.059
Em, I used to be
a bailiff.

19:08.103 --> 19:09.670
I'm still
on the Sheriff's reserve.

19:09.713 --> 19:10.932
And did they call you?

19:10.975 --> 19:12.281
I left my uniform
at the courthouse,

19:12.325 --> 19:14.022
and no, they didn't.

19:14.065 --> 19:16.981
Oh, can you just pleasestop it with the tie?

19:17.025 --> 19:20.028
Please?I'm tired of sitting
on my ass, Em.

19:20.071 --> 19:22.726
Luke, I am doinga virtual bench trial

19:22.770 --> 19:25.381
for my client who isgiving away a boatload

19:25.425 --> 19:28.341
of his constitutional rights
because it is so dangerous.

19:28.384 --> 19:30.473
I'll wear gloves.
I've got a mask.

19:30.517 --> 19:33.302
No. Look at me. Look at me.Look at me. Look at my face.

19:33.346 --> 19:37.219
[ breathing heavily ]
Pick up the phone.

19:37.263 --> 19:40.222
Call who you need to call,okay? Get a list together

19:40.266 --> 19:43.007
of inmates who aredue to be released.

19:43.051 --> 19:44.618
You can help themby finding housing,

19:44.661 --> 19:46.402
by finding other services
that they need.

19:46.446 --> 19:49.318
That's one of the reasons thateveryone is so bogged down.

19:49.362 --> 19:51.668
Don't go down there.

19:51.712 --> 19:55.194
Please.

19:55.237 --> 19:56.369
♪♪♪

19:56.412 --> 19:57.935
[ exhales deeply ]

19:57.979 --> 19:59.850
D.J. TAILWIND:
Don't get comfortable.

19:59.894 --> 20:01.635
Don't get cozy
with that warm cup of coffee

20:01.678 --> 20:03.332
or that hot, hot tea,

20:03.376 --> 20:07.249
'cause there's still some peoplewe need to take heed of--

20:07.293 --> 20:08.859
some people who can't
hear the music--

20:08.903 --> 20:11.253
people who are exposed.

20:11.297 --> 20:14.648
Question is, what are wedoing
to help those

20:14.691 --> 20:16.215
who can't always help
themselves?

20:16.258 --> 20:19.218
♪ ...in the heart of the town,
oh ♪

20:19.261 --> 20:21.045
[ chime ]

20:21.089 --> 20:24.571
Hello? Anyone?

20:24.614 --> 20:29.489
Bueller? Bueller?

20:29.532 --> 20:30.577
[ chime ]

20:30.620 --> 20:33.580
[ gasps ]
Oh, this is fun.

20:33.623 --> 20:36.583
Hey, Sara. How you holding up?

20:36.626 --> 20:38.933
Oh, great.
How are you, Your Honor?

20:38.976 --> 20:41.240
Great. Are you really great?

20:41.283 --> 20:44.939
I'm terrified and anxious,
and I can't sleep.

20:44.982 --> 20:49.291
Yeah. Me, too. Have you been
listening to that D.J.?

20:49.335 --> 20:51.685
- D.J. Tailwind Turner.
- Yes!

20:51.728 --> 20:54.296
Oh, my God. He is
my new internet boyfriend.

20:54.340 --> 20:57.517
Listen. I am a judge
and a happily married woman,

20:57.560 --> 21:00.476
but that man makes me wanna
break the law, okay?

21:00.520 --> 21:01.869
[ chime ]Judge Carmichael?

21:01.912 --> 21:03.610
Please mute and turn offyour video

21:03.653 --> 21:05.438
until the courtis in session.

21:05.481 --> 21:06.787
If we're gonna do this,we're gonna do it right.

21:06.830 --> 21:09.790
Hmm. I will see you soon,
Sara.

21:09.833 --> 21:12.227
[ chime ][ typing on keyboard ]

21:12.271 --> 21:14.273
Ooh! That's pretty!

21:14.316 --> 21:16.536
[ types ]

21:16.579 --> 21:19.756
[ deep voice ]
Courtrooms in space!

21:19.800 --> 21:21.062
[ chime ]

21:21.105 --> 21:23.064
This must be the place.[ chime ]

21:23.107 --> 21:24.674
Hey, Em.

21:24.718 --> 21:27.068
Hey, Sara. I-I can't--

21:27.111 --> 21:29.810
- Is my client here yet?
- Do you see your client?

21:29.853 --> 21:32.987
I hate this already.

21:33.030 --> 21:34.205
[ chime ]

21:34.249 --> 21:36.338
Kurt! Good. You made it.

21:36.382 --> 21:38.079
SHERRI: Oh, wait.Where did I go?

21:38.122 --> 21:40.386
Oh, guys, I think
we've been hacked.

21:40.429 --> 21:42.779
No, it's me. I need to puteverybody in their place.

21:46.348 --> 21:48.089
All rise.

21:48.132 --> 21:51.135
- Are we seriously doing this?
- I'm glad I wore pants.

21:51.179 --> 21:52.311
[ chairs clatter ]

21:52.354 --> 21:53.921
[ chime ]

21:53.964 --> 21:56.271
Ooh. Okay. This is gonna take
some getting used to.

21:56.315 --> 21:59.143
Everyone, please, sit down.

21:59.187 --> 22:00.362
Department 61

22:00.406 --> 22:02.059
of the Los Angeles CountySuperior Court

22:02.103 --> 22:03.234
is now in session.

22:03.278 --> 22:04.714
Judge Lola Carmichaelpresiding.

22:04.758 --> 22:08.805
That means we are nowlive streaming to the internet.

22:08.849 --> 22:11.808
Can everyone see and hear me?

22:11.852 --> 22:13.680
- Mm-hmm.
- Yes, Your Honor.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.769
- Yes, Your Honor.
- Welcome.

22:15.812 --> 22:17.814
We are no longer in our kitchensor our bedrooms.

22:17.858 --> 22:21.078
We are in Courtroom 802.
I expect decorum.

22:21.122 --> 22:22.689
If you wish to be heard
or want to make an objection,

22:22.732 --> 22:25.039
you will raise your hand.

22:25.082 --> 22:28.347
So calling the matter of
The People vs. Kurt Beto.

22:28.390 --> 22:30.610
- Counsel, your appearances.
- Emily Lopez,

22:30.653 --> 22:32.916
Deputy Public Defender,
on his behalf.

22:32.960 --> 22:34.353
Deputy District Attorney
Mark Callan for the People.

22:34.396 --> 22:37.921
Very well. Mr. Beto,
I will address you now.

22:37.965 --> 22:40.924
- Can you hear me?
- Yes, Your Honor.

22:40.968 --> 22:43.013
Do you understand that you are
waiving certain rights

22:43.057 --> 22:45.320
by taking part
in this online bench trial?

22:45.364 --> 22:48.367
The right to face your accuser
in person,

22:48.410 --> 22:50.760
the right to a trial by jury,

22:50.804 --> 22:52.719
and while you retain the right
to appeal

22:52.762 --> 22:54.373
on the merits of this case,

22:54.416 --> 22:57.071
you are waiving the right
to appeal on the procedures.

22:57.114 --> 22:58.551
Do you agree?

22:58.594 --> 22:59.552
Yes, Your Honor.

22:59.595 --> 23:03.338
Mr. Callan, you may begin.

23:03.382 --> 23:04.470
The evidence will show
that Kurt Beto

23:04.513 --> 23:05.601
took from his brother

23:05.645 --> 23:07.864
Joey Beto's possession
a vehicle.

23:07.908 --> 23:09.431
He used force
and intimidation.

23:09.475 --> 23:10.867
It's a carjacking,
plain and simple,

23:10.911 --> 23:12.391
and Kurt Beto
is guilty.

23:12.434 --> 23:13.653
[ Chicano Batman's "Bella"
playing ]

23:13.696 --> 23:15.263
[ chime ]

23:15.306 --> 23:19.006
I've been wearing the same thingfor, like, five days?

23:19.049 --> 23:21.312
And thank God
you can't smell me,

23:21.356 --> 23:23.314
'cause, whoo, boy.

23:23.358 --> 23:24.446
What are you doing?
Studying?

23:24.490 --> 23:27.144
- Making a list.
- That's fun.

23:27.188 --> 23:28.407
All my roommates
deserted me.

23:28.450 --> 23:31.279
I am here alone,
drinking margaritas.

23:31.322 --> 23:32.802
Sam, are you okay?

23:32.846 --> 23:34.804
There areseveral instances
a day

23:34.848 --> 23:36.980
when my cortisol levels
skyrocket.

23:37.024 --> 23:39.809
Hmm.One is when I'm playing
sidewalk chicken

23:39.853 --> 23:41.463
with someone
coming toward me and...[ laughs ]

23:41.507 --> 23:43.596
...another is when
I check the news.

23:43.639 --> 23:45.511
What kind of lists?

23:45.554 --> 23:47.034
Uh, inmates. [ clears throat ]The ones that we're releasing.

23:47.077 --> 23:48.339
I'm trying to findsupport services

23:48.383 --> 23:50.167
for the ones that havenowhere to go.

23:50.211 --> 23:52.082
- Can I help?
- Aren't you hammered?

23:52.126 --> 23:55.477
I'm funny when I'm drunk,
and tequila makes me charming.

23:55.521 --> 23:57.697
Send me the names.
I need to feel useful.

23:57.740 --> 23:59.525
You got it. Thank you.

23:59.568 --> 24:01.701
The People call Joey Beto
to the stand.

24:01.744 --> 24:04.051
Mr. Beto, can you tell us,
please,

24:04.094 --> 24:06.140
who actually owned
the car?

24:06.183 --> 24:07.489
Technically, we both did,

24:07.533 --> 24:09.317
insofar as we
were both on the title.

24:09.360 --> 24:11.232
Can you explain?

24:11.275 --> 24:13.974
I was trying to be nice.
All right, but I paid for it.

24:14.017 --> 24:17.847
All of it. I bought the car.
I paid the insurance.

24:17.891 --> 24:20.284
Marking People's exhibits
1 and 2,

24:20.328 --> 24:22.504
pre-marked PDF. Can you
tell us what they are?

24:22.548 --> 24:24.811
That was the bank draft
in the amount

24:24.854 --> 24:26.247
of $8,200 for the car.

24:26.290 --> 24:28.641
- And this one?
- That's the insurance policy

24:28.684 --> 24:31.295
with my name on it--
Joey Beto.

24:31.339 --> 24:33.559
I even paid three years
of his rent.

24:33.602 --> 24:35.212
I gave him
so much money--

24:35.256 --> 24:38.172
Objection! Objection.
Your Honor. Relevance?

24:38.215 --> 24:40.609
Just a second--Your Honor, the brothers'
past relationship

24:40.653 --> 24:41.871
is very relevant.Hang on.

24:41.915 --> 24:43.917
Ms. Kansky, do we have
the exhibits?

